I can confirm that the boulder at (8,10) is pushable, the one at (5,12) and (9,14) are immovable. The last boulder is at (2,13). Now, the last boulder at (2,13), it's only able to be pushed North. I will check the position to see if I am able to push the boulder. So, it is located at 2,13.  I need to go from 2,13 -> 2,12 -> 2,11 -> 2,10. I see that that I cannot move it East to get to the fountain. This is likely another dead end.

I have found my answer. The boulder at 8,10 can be pushed, and the other 3 boulders are placed in positions where they cannot be pushed. I cannot move the boulders at 5,12 and 9,14. Then the only one left is 2,13, but the character positions prevent this from being able to be pushed onto the fountain. It's a classic Sokoban puzzle - push those boulders onto the sparkly spots!  So it's unsolvable.  There are three fountains, but only one boulder can be successfully pushed onto a fountain.","message:


